<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>PvP Tactics</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Antwon">Antwon</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 6:48 a.m. 5/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> PvP Tactics<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Well,

<P>I am playing a Necro (most of the time) on the PvP server. Pking with this character has become almost boring because the same thing seems to work almost every time.
<P>I cast Fear (target runs, can not cast spells)
<BR>I stick my pet on target
<BR>I cast Engulfing Darkness (slows target, Pet hits more <G>)
<BR>I cast Heat Blood
<BR>(I would then cast Heart Flutter, if I reached 16th)
<P>I then Life Drain till target dies
<P>If they start doing anything else but running.. I fear again
<P>Although it works well.. and as I gain more levels I simply upgrade the drain, darkness, blood, and heart spells with the higher level equvialents.. I dont like that one tactic is always working.
<P>So I ask the PvP people here...
<P>How do you counter the method I am using?
<P>Antwon
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
